| Sponsor company   | 

### What is it about
- Category has two images. One is stored in `ID.jpg`, the second in `ID_thumb.jpg`.
- The logic is currently broken and when you want to get category image in front office, you randomly get a different image in small_default array.

### What this fixes
- You can now get both images in all dimensions via functions I prepared earlier in `CategoryLazyArray`. Just by calling `$category->thumbnail`, `$category->cover`.
- [BC break] No image is now returned by default, if the image does not exist. Theme can decide what to do. Now, it didn't have a chance to know if the image was returned or the placeholder was returned.
- You can now manage both images in backoffice separately.
  - They are not overwriting each other anymore.
  - Changing cover doesn't change thumbnail anymore.
  - You can delete both images separately.
  - Thumbnails are correctly deleted in all formats.
- `.htaccess` rules have been added to rewrite links to these images.
- Both cover and thumbnail is correctly generated when using regeneration function in backoffice.
- Simplifies and speeds up thumbnail deletion, because it uses one regex to check if it's a thumbnail.

### Theme change required
- Changing `$category->image` to `$category->thumbnail` and `$category->cover`.
- If image does not exist, optionally render `$urls.no_picture_image`.
- See example in this PR - https://github.com/PrestaShop/classic-theme/pull/154

----------

### Autoupgrade PR logic
```php
/*
 * Pre v9 worked like this:
 * There could be 123.jpg, a cover image.
 * There could be 123_thumb.jpg, a category miniature.
 * 
 * If 123_thumb.jpg existed, it took it and generated category thumbnails from it.
 * But, overwriting thumbnails of 123.jpg.
 *
 * So you suddenly got one thumbnail that was from a different image.
 * Even worse, frontoffice and backoffice generated it as a different thumbnail.
 */
$formattedNameSmall = ImageType::getFormattedName('small');
$formattedNameMedium = ImageType::getFormattedName('medium');

foreach ($categoryIds as $categoryId) {
  /*
   * Define paths to original files.
   * Define paths to possible broken thumbnails.
   */
  $categoryCoverPath = _PS_CAT_IMG_DIR_ . $categoryId . '.jpg';
  $categoryMiniaturePath = _PS_CAT_IMG_DIR_ . $categoryId . '_thumb.jpg';
  $categorySmallPath =_PS_CAT_IMG_DIR_ . $categoryId . '-' . $formattedNameSmall . '.jpg';
  $categoryMediumPath = _PS_CAT_IMG_DIR_ . $categoryId . '-' . $formattedNameMedium . '.jpg';

  // Check what images exist
  $hasCover = file_exists($categoryCoverPath);
  $hasMiniature = file_exists($categoryMiniaturePath);
  
  /*
   * If both exist, generated thumbnails can be wrong.
   * We delete them and we are finished.
   */
  if ($hasCover && $hasMiniature) {
    if (file_exists($categorySmallPath)) {
      unlink($categorySmallPath);
    }
    if (file_exists($categoryMediumPath)) {
      unlink($categoryMediumPath);
    }
  }

  /*
   * If it has a cover but no thumbnail, we don't want people
   * to end up with no thumbnail. We will copy the cover
   * as the thumbnail. 
   */
  if ($hasCover && !$hasMiniature) {
    copy($categoryCoverPath, $categoryMiniaturePath);
  }

  /*
   * If it has a thumbnail but no cover, we will delete thumbnails,
   * because they have a wrong name and we don't want them to make
   * issues.
   */
  if (!$hasCover && $hasMiniature) {
    if (file_exists($categorySmallPath)) {
      unlink($categorySmallPath);
    }
    if (file_exists($categoryMediumPath)) {
      unlink($categoryMediumPath);
    }
  }
}
```
